1. Images
- A machine image is a compute engine resource that stores all the
  configuration, metadata, permissions and data from one or more disks required
  to create a virtual machine instance.
- Public base images
- Custom images:
  - Create new image from VM: pre-configured and installed VM.
  - Import from on-prem, workstation, or another cloud.
  - Management features: image sharing, image family, deprecation.

2. Scenario:
Scenarios                     |Machine|Persistent    |Custom image|Instance 
                              |_image_|disk snapshots|            |template
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Single disk backup            | Yes   | Yes          | Yes        | No
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Multiple disk backup          | Yes   | No           | No         | No
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Differential backup           | Yes   | Yes          | No         | No
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Instance cloning & replication| Yes   | No           | Yes        | Yes
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
VM instance configuration     | Yes   | No           | No         | Yes
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
